body:
Movidius designs the most advanced vision processing chip architectures. You could change the world by contributing to this technology!

For junior candidates, any form of Verilog/VHDL experience and understanding of the hardware design flow from high level specifications down to FPGA/ASIC technology. Knowledge of assembly languages or any form of embedded SW programming is a plus.

For senior candidates, the ideal candidate will have:
- 4+ years experience specifying and designing complex digital functions for System-on-Chip ICs;
- Knowledge of various computer architectures;
- Familiarity with any of the Verilog, VHDL, SystemC HDLs and CAD tools from leading vendors such as Synopsys, Cadence and Mentor Graphics;
- Experience developing and running comprehensive verification tests;
- A strong background in best industry practice for IC design;
- An honors degree qualification in electronic engineering or related discipline;
- The ability to work well in a team;
- Experience managing team members;
- Background with Processor-based SoC architectures and low power design techniques;

The Movidius team works with the latest design flows and methods for international chip customers on leading edge product design.

The work will be through the English language and an ability to read and write technical English is required.
